  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is an indexing conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>An indexing conveyor advances product a fixed distance and holds it stationary for a downstream operation. Each start-stop cycle positions product at a precise dwell point for filling, labeling, pick-and-place, inspection, or assembly. Positioning accuracy ranges from &plusmn;2mm (pneumatic stops) to &plusmn;0.1mm (servo-driven belt or pallet transfer).</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            Servo indexing vs. mechanical indexing?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Servo indexing uses programmable servo motors , change index length, speed, dwell, and motion profile through the HMI. Mechanical indexing uses cams or Geneva drives with fixed motion profiles. Servo costs more but enables recipe-based changeover for multi-SKU lines. Mechanical provides reliable, maintenance-simple operation for dedicated single-format applications.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What accuracy can indexing conveyors achieve?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Servo belt: &plusmn;0.1–0.5mm. Timing screw: &plusmn;0.25mm. Mechanical cam: &plusmn;0.5–1.0mm. Pallet transfer: &plusmn;0.05–0.1mm. Pneumatic stops: &plusmn;1.0–2.0mm. Choose the technology based on your downstream operation's positioning tolerance.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What industries use indexing conveyors?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Food and beverage (filling, capping, labeling), pharmaceutical (blister packing, vial filling), cosmetics (tube filling, compact assembly), automotive (parts assembly), and electronics (PCB handling). Any operation requiring precise product positioning for a timed process uses indexing conveyors.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
